data.text:
Blacksmith Shop - National Parks Gallery

The Blacksmith Shop at Herbert Hoover National Historic Site resembles the shop that Jesse Hoover owned in the 1870s.

Herbert Hoover's birthday celebration, Herbert Hoover National Histori...

President Hoover celebrating his 80th birthday inside the same two-room cottage where he was born in West Branch. This party took place at the boy scout picnic shelter.

Hoover family picnic, 1878 - Public Domain image, National Parks Galle...

Extended Hoover family (young Herbert is in the back, in his father's arms left of the boy in the tree), 1878

Newspaper Advertisement, 1877 - National Parks Gallery

An 1877 newspaper advertisement for J.C. Hoover's blacksmith shop Public domain photograph related to US National Parks, Nature, conservation, free to use, no copyright restrictions image - Picryl description

National parks: Schoolhouse - public domain image

West Branch used the one-room schoolhouse for the early primary grades when Herbert Hoover entered school in 1879.

Hulda Hoover (1848-1884), Herbert Hoover National Historic Site, 2015.

Photo date unknown. Hulda Hoover was a leader in the Quaker church. She traveled to speak at meetings in other towns. She also led youth prayer meetings and took an active role in prohibition campaigns.

Statue of Isis - National Parks Gallery

The people of Belgium presented “Isis, Goddess of Life” to Hoover as a gift of gratitude.

Visitor Center in Herbert Hoover national historic site

Start your visit with an introduction to Herbert Hoover and his hometown of West Branch.

Herbert Hoover Presidential Library and Museum

Museum galleries tell of the triumphs and tragedies of Hoover’s long career in public service.
